Operatives of the Lagos State Police Command have arrested a woman for allegedly killing her husband in the Abule-Egba area of the state. The deceased, Alaba Bakare aka Bama, who owned the popular Bama Hotel and Suites, reportedly recently arrived from Dubai with his wife and three children. The wife simply identified as Motunrayo, got information that her husband had impregnated another lady, reportedly drugged her husband on Monday night, and placed a hot iron on parts of his body until he died. 2023: Be Interested In Who Succeeds You, Ohaneze Tells Buhari INEC Nominee: 7 Months After Onochie’s Rejection, Buhari… The State Police Public Relations Officer, CSP Ade Ajisebutu, who confirmed her arrest, said, “The body has been deposited at the Yaba Mainland Hospital’s morgue for autopsy. “The deceased’s wife and three others have been arrested in connection with the suspected murder case.”